    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to a statistical technique, a form of multivariate analysis, used by archaeologists and conservation scientists in conjunction with multispectral analysis to organize compositional data among a set of objects, such as the differential distribution and concentrations of a metallic element in ceramics.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
